

=Discussion=

Mike Chege:

"Commodification may be described as the process by which the market establishes property rights and excluding devices to facilitate the production and exchange of wealth. In the software industry, excluding devices may include legal devices such as software licenses, and physical devices such as copy restriction and product activation codes."



